<DOC><DOCNO> AP890220-0104 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-20-89 1710EST</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-BRF--Italy-Pileup 1stLd-Writethru a0598 02-20 0148</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Italy-Pileup, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0598,0149</SECOND><HEAD>200 Cars, Trucks Pile Up on Foggy Roads, Kill 13</HEAD><HEAD>Eds: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with 13 dead and more than 100 injured</HEAD><DATELINE>PIACENZA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Nearly 200 cars and trucks slammed intoeach other in separate accidents Monday on fog-bound highways innorthern and central Italy. Police said 13 people were killed andmore than 100 injured.   Two major pileups occurred during morning rush hour near Piacenzain the north and near Imola and Ferrara in central Italy. Thick fogreduced visibility to near zero, police said.   Highways from Milan to Modena and Bologna to Ferrara _ two majorroad links _ were closed for about five hours after the accidents.   Police said most of the injured were hospitalized in Piacenza.   Large parts of Italy have been plagued by fog and smog in recentweeks following three months without rain.</TEXT></DOC>